Class viewMap

java.lang.Object
viewMap
All Implemented Interfaces:
ActionListener, MouseMotionListener, EventListener
public class viewMap extends Object implements ActionListener, MouseMotionListener
This class implements the functionality for viewing a map of a particular building on a particular floor. It also includes various user interface components like a toolbar, a search bar, and a menu bar.
Version:
1.0
Author:
Yuting Pan, Yi Xiao

  • Constructor Details

    • viewMap

      public viewMap(String buildingName) throws SQLException, ClassNotFoundException
      This class represents the view of a map for a given building. It includes various UI components such as menus, buttons, checkboxes, and labels, as well as a panel to display the map.
      Parameters:
      buildingName - the name of the building for which to display the map
      Throws:
      SQLException - if there is an error executing a database query
      ClassNotFoundException - if the JDBC driver for the database cannot be found

      public void refreshFavorite() throws SQLException, ClassNotFoundException
      Refreshes the favorite list by getting the user's favorite list and adding it to the menu bar. Also adds action listeners to each item in the favorite list.
      Throws:
      SQLException - if a database access error occurs
      ClassNotFoundException - if the database driver class is not found
